        "content": "<p>Hi everybody :)</p>\n<p>I wanted to use sum_range_succ in a proof, but I am very confused about this theorem.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/o5i3ovBlWQ2C_u2d3KWzA86M/sum_range_succ.png\">sum_range_succ.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/o5i3ovBlWQ2C_u2d3KWzA86M/sum_range_succ.png\" title=\"sum_range_succ.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/o5i3ovBlWQ2C_u2d3KWzA86M/sum_range_succ.png\"></a></div><p>I found this in the Lean 4 documentation side. Why do they add f n at the end and not f (n+1). The last \"element\" of the sum is (n+1) and not n.</p>\n<p>What am I missing?</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance!<br>\nMatt</p>",
